		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2014 SI"></a><br><code>sle2014s/paper04</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2014 SI</a> paper:</span><br><i>Intra- and interdiagram consistency checking of behavioral multiview models</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/PetraKaufmann.html">Petra Kaufmann</a>, <a href="../profile/MartinKronegger.html">Martin Kronegger</a>, <a href="../profile/AndreasPfandler.html">Andreas Pfandler</a>, <a href="../profile/MartinaSeidl.html">Martina Seidl</a>, <a href="../profile/MagdalenaWidl.html">Magdalena Widl</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cl.2015.08.003">10.1016/j.cl.2015.08.003</a></li>
<li>Extended version of <a href="../sle2014/paper02.html"><em>A SAT-Based Debugging Tool for State Machines and Sequence Diagrams</em></a> (SLE 2014)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagM">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> The contribution is a formal consistency-checking method for behavioral models (with SAT solving as the underlying decision procedure).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagL">T5B: Language Description Analysis</span></a><ul><li> It analyses language artifacts (behavioral UML models/diagrams) to detect and explain inconsistencies across views.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The work targets a domain/purpose-specific modeling setting (behavioral multiview models) rather than general-purpose programming.
</li></ul></li></ul>
		<clear/>
